issue.title: fix(discussions): find closest discussion comment or reply by timestamp
issue.body:
**Problem**
Earlier today I noticed several discussion notifications which were showing an incorrect actor profile image, and upon notification interaction deep-linking to the wrong discussion item (latest comment instead of most recent reply on an older comment thread).

**Solution**
Updating our logic to find the latest discussion comment or reply to instead find the closest/nearest in timestamp. 

In order to increase the accuracy, we have to fetch a wider selection of comments or replies before filtering down

### üìã Checklist

- [X] I‚Äôm running **the latest `main` or a recent release**.
- [X] I‚Äôve searched existing issues‚ÄÇand **no open issue covers this bug**.
- [ ] If this is a build problem, I attached the **full error log**.

---

### What version?

kingfisher 1.31.0

### üêû  What happened?

I have a private Github repo that has some old secrets exposed. Among those are some unexpired JWTs that are picked up by the `--only-valid` flag so I wanted to establish a baseline. When I run `kingfisher scan . --manage-baseline --baseline-file ./baseline-file.yml`, I see a lot of `.git/**` entries that don't seem like they need to be there, so I modified the command to exclude that directory: `kingfisher scan . --exclude='.git' --manage-baseline --baseline-file ./baseline-file.yml`, but the .git baseline entries persist.

### ‚úÖ  What did you expect to happen?

I may be misunderstanding this, but I'd think that the `--exclude .git` (I've tried variations like `./.git` and `.git/`, etc.) would keep those out of the baseline file.

### üî¢  Reproduction steps

1. In a local git repo, run `kingfisher scan . --exclude .git --manage-baseline --baseline-file ./baseline-file.yml`
2. Open `./baselin-file.yml` and search for `.git/` entries

| Item            | Value |

issue.title: Create comprehensive migration strategy for mixin fields (#195)
issue.body:
## Summary

Implements a comprehensive migration strategy for safely applying mixin fields to existing Django models as requested in issue #195.

### Key Components Delivered:

‚úÖ **21 Migration Safety Tests** (`core/tests/test_migration_strategy.py`)
- Data preservation across forward/backward migrations  
- Default value application and audit field population
- Data integrity maintenance (FK constraints, unique constraints, cascades)
- Edge case handling (null values, long names, user deletion, timestamps)
- Performance testing with realistic data volumes (up to 100 objects)
- Concurrency testing for post-migration behavior
- Rollback safety and atomicity verification
- Audit trail integration testing

‚úÖ **Data Migration Files** (addresses audit field population)
- `characters/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `player_owner` for audit fields
- `items/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `campaign.owner` for audit fields  
- `locations/migrations/0004_populate_audit_fields.py` - Uses `campaign.owner` for audit fields
- All migrations include proper rollback functionality

‚úÖ **Automated Rollback Script** (`scripts/rollback_mixin_migrations.sh`)
- Interactive safety confirmations
- Step-by-step rollback process (data migrations first, then schema)
- Environment detection and progress reporting
- Complete rollback of both schema (0003) and data (0004) migrations

‚úÖ **Comprehensive Documentation** (`docs/MIGRATION_STRATEGY.md`)
- Pre-migration checklists and safety procedures
- Step-by-step production deployment guidelines
- Post-migration validation procedures
- Performance considerations and monitoring guidance
- Troubleshooting section with common issues and solutions

### Migration Strategy Overview:

**Schema Migrations (0003):**
- Add `created_by`, `modified_by` fields to Character, Item, Location models
- Update timestamp field configurations for proper indexing
- Enhance name field with standardized help text

**Data Migrations (0004):**  
- Populate audit fields with sensible defaults for existing records
- Characters: Use `player_owner` (most logical ownership)
- Items/Locations: Use `campaign.owner` (campaign-level resources)
- Atomic operations with proper error handling

### Testing Results:
- **All 1210 tests passing** ‚úÖ (including the 21 new migration safety tests)
- **Zero regressions** - All existing functionality preserved
- **Migration safety validated** - Data preservation, integrity, and rollback confirmed

### Production Safety Features:
- Comprehensive test coverage ensuring zero data loss
- Multiple rollback options (automated script + manual procedures)
- Performance testing validates migrations complete in reasonable time
- Edge case testing covers real-world scenarios (user deletion, constraints, etc.)

### Documentation Updates:
- Enhanced `docs/development-guide.md` with migration testing procedures
- Updated `docs/database-schema.md` with migration strategy documentation
- Enhanced `docs/deployment.md` with production migration procedures
- Integrated with existing `CLAUDE.md` development workflow

## Test Plan

‚úÖ Migration safety tests (21 tests) - All passing
‚úÖ Full test suite (1210 tests) - All passing  
‚úÖ Data preservation verified
‚úÖ Rollback procedures tested
‚úÖ Documentation comprehensive and validated

performed_via_github_app.description:
SonarQube Cloud (formerly SonarCloud) is a SaaS code analysis tool designed to detect coding issues in 30+ languages, frameworks, and IaC platforms. Your code is checked against an extensive set of rules that cover many attributes of code, such as maintainability, reliability, and security issues, on each merge/pull request.

For those requiring US-based hosting, [SonarQube Cloud US](https://sonarqube.us/) offers the perfect alternative. If you need data residency outside the US or within the EU, [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/) with this GitHub app is the ideal solution.

SonarQube Cloud integrates seamlessly into your GitHub workflow and provides clear guidance for resolving any code quality and security issues detected. The majority of popular languages can be analyzed automatically; no configuration is required!

With [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/github), you get:

-   Fast, precise static analysis and feedback on your code
    
-   Support for popular languages, frameworks, and IaC tools
    
-   Free analysis for open-source projects and private projects up to max 50k LoC
    
-   Automatic analysis of pull requests and branches with results reported inline
    
-   IDE Support with [SonarQube for IDE](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarlint/) integration
    
-   Quality Gate (added as a GitHub check) acting at two different levels - first, preventing you from merging pull requests that contain issues - and later, helping you to release only clean, safe code
    
-   Sign up for SonarQube free tier and begin scanning your private and public repositories
    

A [GitHub Action](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/sonarcloud-scan) is available in the marketplace to make it easy for you (for projects where automatic analysis isn't available). SonarQube Cloud also integrates smoothly with Jenkins, CircleCI, TravisCI, CirrusCI, and many other tools.

A free tier is available that allows you to explore the benefits of SonarQube Cloud using your public and private repositories. We also provide a no-commitment, [14-day trial](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/) of SonarQube Cloud Team for unlimited team members, up to 1.9M LoC, AI CodeFix recommendations, and more. No need to speak with a sales rep or request a license key - get automatic code analysis results on your private projects in minutes! Want to see more examples of SonarCloud in action? You can [explore current Open Source projects in SonarCloud](https://sonarcloud.io/explore/projects?sort=-analysis_date) that are using the [Clean as You Code](https://www.sonarsource.com/solutions/our-unique-approach/) methodology.

What are you waiting for? SonarQube Cloud helps you consistently deliver cleaner, secure software that future developers will appreciate and your users will love. Start writing Clean Code. [Now](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarcloud/signup/)!

        httpOnly: res.httpOnly,
        sameSite: res.sameSite,
